    <text type="letter">
        <body>
            <pb xml:id="leaf001r" facs="loc.01168.002_large.jpg" type="recto"/>
            <opener>
                <dateline>
                    <name type="place">Camden</name>
                    <date when="1889-05-17">May 17 '89<ptr target="loc.01168_n1"/></date>
                </dateline>
            </opener>
            <p>As I write (noon) I have not heard a word since from Wash'n but of course our dear
                    friend<ptr target="n2002"/> is buried<ptr target="loc.01168_n2"/> &#38; all has
                gone like tracks on the shore by sea waves washed away passing&#8212;</p>
            <p>&#8212;Much the same with me (gradually yielding)&#8212;One betterment&#8212;I get
                out in a wheel'd chair,<ptr target="loc.03012_n1"/> often twice a day&#8212;am sitting here by the open
                window&#8212;perfect weather&#8212;</p> 
            <closer>
                <salute>best love&#8212;</salute>
                <signed>Walt Whitman</signed>
            </closer>
            <pb xml:id="leaf001v" facs="loc.01168.001_large.jpg" type="verso"/>
            <note type="editorial" place="top" resp="#unk">6 | 5/17/89</note>
        </body>
